description:
When 8-yr-old Mac is forced to give up his Imaginary Friend Bloo, they find Foster's Home for Imaginary Friends, an amazing house for unwanted Imaginary Friends.

Synopsis

After a conflict with his brother, Mac is forced to give up his imaginary friend Bloo by his mom. Unwilling to be separated from one another, Bloo discovers Foster's Home for Imaginary friends, a home for imaginary friends. Initially excited Bloo proposes to stay at Foster's instead. However, they discover that there's is a catch; Foster's is a foster home and all friends there are up for adoption.

description: DEATHSTROKE HITS OLIVER AT HOME — Oliver (Stephen Amell), Canary (Caity Lotz), Diggle (David Ramsey) and Felicity (Emily Bett Rickards) return to the lair and find Slade (Manu Bennett) waiting for them. An epic battle breaks out and one member of Team Arrow is sent to the hospital. Thea (Willa Holland) hits her breaking point, but just as Oliver is about to reach her, Slade intervenes and Oliver is faced with a choice – his battle with Slade or his family. Meanwhile, Laurel (Katie Cassidy) struggles with a new secret. Jesse Warn directed the episode with story by Greg Berlanti & Geoff Johns and teleplay by Andrew Kreisberg & Keto Shimizu.

description:
The Origin of the Hulk

Doctor Bruce Banner creates a Gamma Bomb for the army. When the young Rick Jones drives onto the test area for a dare, at the day the army wants to test the bomb, Banner goes to rescue him, only to be caught in the explosion himself. As the sun sets, the radiation transforms Bruce Banner into a green skinned goliath. The Incredible Hulk is born.

Enter the Gorgon

The Hulk catches Igor Drenkov in Banner's home, where the Russian spy tried to steal Banners gamma ray formula, but Drenkov is soon overwhelmed by the green creature. When Hulk finds a photograph of Banner, he states his hate for the puny scientist and pushes Rick Jones away, when the teenager tries to tell him, the he is Bruce Banner. Just before the Hulk is about to smash Jones, the sun rises and he transforms back into Doctor Bruce Banner. Drenkov gets thrown into prison by the entering army, and sends a radio message to the Gorgon from his cell.

To Be a Man

The Gorgon intrudes America to find the Hulk and destroy him. Meanwhile Doctor Banner and Rick Jones drive down a street, when the sun sets again and the good Doctor becomes the Hulk again. Only caring about wanting to see Betty Ross, the Hulk walks to her house, where his look makes her faint. The Gorgon uses this moment to approach Hulk and Rick Jones and shoots a mind controlling bullet at each of them and takes both of them with him to Russia. Inside the rocket of the Gorgon, the Hulk turns back into Banner. A desperate Gorgon then begs Banner to help him, to turn him back into a human. After Banner's help, Gorgon sets him and Jones free and kills himself with a bomb, so that he can die as a man.
name: The Origin of the Hulk; Enter the Gorgon; To Be a Man

description:
Terror of the Toadmen

A spaceship full of the terrible aliens is on the way to earth. Meanwhile Hulk wreaks havoc in the town, until Rick Jones manages to lead him away from it. When the sun rises, Hulk transform back into Bruce Banner, who figured out, that it is the night, which turns him into the Hulk. Together with Rick, goes Banner into the desert, where he finds an old cave and rebuilds it into a refuge, so he can lock Hulk away over night. Soon the Toadmen arrive and kidnap Banner and Jones into their spaceship. In the spaceship they threaten Banner and Jones and soon send the teenager back to earth. As the ship orbits into the night the good doctor turns once again into the Hulk and rages through it.

Bruce Banner: Wanted For Treason!

The army shoots rockets at the alien ship and brings it down. When Banner emerges out of the wreckage General Ross lets have him arrested for treason. Meanwhile, the Toadmen escape through a tunnel and signal their fleet to invade the earth. The Toadmen in space threaten mankind with destroying the earth if they don't surrender, but General Ross stands firm. Banner turns again into the Hulk and breaks out of his cell. Hulk then goes to Betty Ross's house.

Hulk Runs Amok

The army surrounds Ross's house and Hulk fights against them. He then kidnaps Betty and brings her into Bruce Banner's house. When she asks him in fear, why he hates them so much, he answers that he hates all of mankind, because they won't stop hunting him. Rick pleads Hulk to stop and to save the earth, as in the same moment the Toadmen's attack makes the ground tremble, which sends the Hulk outside onto the veranda. Outside the rising sun transforms the Hulk back into Bruce Banner. Banner first takes care of Betty and the goes to the Gamma Ray Gun he built, to use it against the Toadmen.
name: Terror of the Toadmen; Bruce Banner: Wanted For Treason!; Hulk Runs Amok
